  "body": "If you try to use our version of Waffle's `loadFixture` when connected to an account other than `buidlerevm`, you'll get an exception.\r\n\r\nThis happens because it calls `waffle.provider.getWallets()` under the hood, and that only works for `buidlerevm`, as `Wallet`s can't be obtained for a remote network.\r\n\r\nI created a PR in Waffle so that we can use `Signer`s there instead of `Wallet`s: https://github.com/EthWorks/Waffle/pull/330\r\n\r\nOnce this PR is merged, we should update the plugin accordingly.",
